<inglise> COMMISSION DECISION of 30 May 1994 laying down detailed rules for the application of Council Directive 93/24/EEC as regards the statistical surveys on cattle population and production, and amending the said Directive (94/433/EC) </inglise>
<eesti> KOMISJONI OTSUS 94/433/E&Uuml;, millega n&auml;hakse ette n&otilde;ukogu direktiivi 93/24/EM&Uuml; &uuml;ksikasjalikud rakenduseeskirjad veisekarjade ja veisekasvatuse statistiliste vaatluste osas ning muudetakse nimetatud direktiivi 30. mai 1994 </eesti>
<inglise> THE COMMISSION OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA &Uuml;HENDUSTE KOMISJON, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Community, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa &Uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to Council Directive 93/24/EEC of 1 June 1993 on the statistical surveys to be carried out on bovine animal production (1), and in particular Articles 1 (3), 2 (2), 3 (2), 6 (1) and (2), 8 (1) and (2), 10 (3) and 12 (2) thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse n&otilde;ukogu 1. juuni 1993. aasta direktiivi 93/24/EM&Uuml; veisekasvatuse statistiliste vaatluste kohta, (1) eriti selle artikli 1 l&otilde;iget 3, artikli 2 l&otilde;iget 2, artikli 3 l&otilde;iget 2, artikli 6 l&otilde;ikeid 1 ja 2, artikli 8 l&otilde;ikeid 1 ja 2 ning artikli 12 l&otilde;iget 2, </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas precise definitions are required in order to carry out the surveys provided for in Directive 93/24/EEC; whereas this requires the definition of the agricultural holdings covered by the survey; whereas the individual categories into which the survey results are to be broken down must be precisely defined, and the herd size classes and regions according to which the Member States draw up the survey results at regular intervals must be determined; whereas a single definition of carcass weight is necessary for the drawing-up of slaughtering statistics; </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestades, et: direktiiviga 93/24/EM&Uuml; etten&auml;htud vaatluste korraldamiseks on vaja t&auml;pseid m&auml;&auml;ratlusi; see n&otilde;uab vaatlusega h&otilde;lmatud p&otilde;llumajandusettev&otilde;tete m&auml;&auml;ratlemist; tuleks t&auml;pselt m&auml;&auml;ratleda eri kategooriad, millesse vaatlustulemused jaotada, ning karja suurusklassid ja piirkonnad, mille p&otilde;hjal liikmesriigid esitavad korrap&auml;raselt vaatlustulemusi; tapastatistika koostamiseks on vaja r&uuml;mba massi &uuml;htset m&auml;&auml;ratlust; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, with the amendment of the combined nomenclature for live bovine animals by Commission Regulation (EEC) No 2505/92 (2), it is no longer possible, either for intra-Community trade or for trade with non-member countries, for the Member States to record trade in bulls and bullocks separately; wheres the breakdown of gross indigenous production into bulls and bullocks required under Council Directive 93/24/EEC is thus no longer possible; whereas Directive 93/24/EEC should therefore be amended; </inglise>
<eesti> komisjoni m&auml;&auml;rusega (EM&Uuml;) nr 2505/92 (2) elusloomade koondnomenklatuuri tehtud muudatuste t&otilde;ttu ei ole &uuml;hendusesiseses kaubanduses v&otilde;i kaubanduses kolmandate riikidega enam v&otilde;imalik teha vahet pullide ja h&auml;rgade vahel; seep&auml;rast ei ole n&otilde;ukogu direktiivi 93/24/EM&Uuml; kohane omamaise kogutoodangu pullideks ja h&auml;rgadeks jaotamine enam v&otilde;imalik; seep&auml;rast tuleks direktiivi 93/24/EM&Uuml; muuta; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, furthermore, according to Directive 93/24/EEC, the Member States may, at their request, be authorized to carry out the May or June surveys in selected regions, on the understanding that these surveys cover at least 70 % of the bovine population; whereas Member States whose bovine population makes up only a small percentage of the overall population of the Community may, at their request, also be authorized to dispense altogether with either the May/June or December surveys, or to use the regional breakdown for the final results of the May/June survey; whereas, finally, the Member States may, at their request, be authorized to use administrative sources instead of statistical surveys to determine the cattle population and the prescribed breakdown by herd size classes for the final results of even-numbered years and/or for the results of the May/June survey; </inglise>
<eesti> lisaks sellele v&otilde;idakse vastavalt direktiivile 93/24/EM&Uuml; lubada liikmesriikidel taotluse korral teha mai- v&otilde;i juunivaatlusi valitud piirkondades, tingimusel et k&otilde;nealused vaatlused h&otilde;lmavad v&auml;hemalt 70% veisekarjast; liikmesriikidel, mille veisekarjad moodustavad &uuml;ksnes v&auml;ikese osa kogu &uuml;henduse veisekarjadest, v&otilde;idakse taotluse korral lubada loobuda t&auml;ielikult kas mai- v&otilde;i juunivaatlustest v&otilde;i detsembrivaatlusest v&otilde;i kasutada mai- v&otilde;i juunivaatluse l&otilde;pptulemustes piirkondlikku jaotust; liikmesriikidel v&otilde;idakse taotluse korral lubada kasutada statistiliste vaatluste asemel haldusallikaid, et m&auml;&auml;rata kindlaks veisekarjad, ja kasutada paarisarvuliste aastate ja/v&otilde;i mai- v&otilde;i juunivaatluse l&otilde;pptulemustes jaotust karja suurusklasside kaupa; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas applications have been made by the Member States for the abovementioned types of authorization; </inglise>
<eesti> liikmesriigid on esitanud taotlusi eespool nimetatud v&otilde;imaluste kasutamiseks; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas Commission Decision 73/262/EEC (3), as amended by Decision 90/501/EEC (4), should be replaced; </inglise>
<eesti> komisjoni otsus 73/262/EM&Uuml;, (3) muudetud otsusega 90/501/EM&Uuml;, (4) tuleks asendada; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, since Directive 93/24/EEC is applicable as from 1 January 1994, it is appropriate to apply the provisions of this Decision with effect from the same date; </inglise>
<eesti> direktiivi 93/24/EM&Uuml; kohaldatakse alates 1. jaanuarist 1994, seep&auml;rast on kohane kohaldada k&auml;esoleva otsuse s&auml;tteid alates samast kuup&auml;evast; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas this Decision is in accordance with the opinion of the Standing Committee on Agricultural Statistics, </inglise>
<eesti> k&auml;esolev otsus on koosk&otilde;las alalise p&otilde;llumajandusstatistika komitee arvamusega, </eesti>
